Everyone should know how to act in case of accidents and sudden illness. Knowledge and skills in first aid give the courage to act and to help in different situations.Objectives/eesmärkid:  After finishing the course the student will have theoretical knowledge of and practical know-how in sudden illnesses in children.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After finishing the course the student should - know  age-related peculiarities of a sick child;  - know how to prepare the child and his/her close relatives for procedures/ investigations;  - be able to dress a wound, to stop bleeding and to render first aid in case of freezing and burn related damages;  - be able to act in case of fever and pain;  - be able to administer the sick child medication.
